techniques and have found their own particular way of teaching this satipanya you see I try to maintain a fairly strict line but I don't think if my teacher were here they'd be happy with my approach either because in the east it's all full on you know it's 18 hours sitting walking sitting walking none of this open awareness space out it's just you know try harder and then

377
00:47:22,422 --> 00:47:24,164
And in the end, it sort of works.

378
00:47:25,264 --> 00:47:26,186
For some people, it didn't.

379
00:47:26,206 --> 00:47:29,268
For some people, it was just the wrong technique.

380
00:47:29,289 --> 00:47:35,695
So this is, as I said at the beginning, this is just an opportunity to investigate yourself.

381
00:47:35,735 --> 00:47:36,297
This is for you.

382
00:47:36,677 --> 00:47:39,300
This is self-caring.

383
00:47:39,320 --> 00:47:41,603
This is trying to do something about ourselves.

384
00:47:42,744 --> 00:47:46,768
With the obvious understanding that when I change, things change around me.

385
00:47:46,947 --> 00:47:47,568
People change.

386
00:47:49,456 --> 00:47:54,840
So take this opportunity to really devote yourself to this practice.

387
00:47:54,860 --> 00:47:58,204
I can only hope my words have been of some assistance.

388
00:47:58,224 --> 00:48:10,275
May by your devoted effort, unrelenting devoted effort, achieve liberation from all suffering sooner rather than later.

389
00:48:16,402 --> 00:48:18,103
That's what you're supposed to say.

390
00:48:18,222 --> 00:48:19,023
Sadhu, sadhu, sadhu.

391
00:48:19,864 --> 00:48:20,445
I'll try again.

392
00:48:20,905 --> 00:48:24,190
May you be fully liberated sooner rather than later.

393
00:48:30,478 --> 00:48:31,280
That makes me feel good.

394
00:48:33,563 --> 00:48:40,172
There were scriptures where the monks and nuns delighted in the Buddha's words.

